node.text:
"I’m not a catastrophist. There are many wonderful people teaching in many institutions around the world... While I say that, the universities have by and large fundamentally forgotten, if not betrayed, their fundamental value proposition."⁣
⁣
My latest podcast with Dr. Stephen Blackwood is now live on YouTube, Apple Podcasts and Spotify. ⁣
⁣
We discuss the inner workings of philosophical aspects about social constructs, the spiritual ‘culture crisis’, what it means to live as an individual in a time of spiritual, cultural crisis, and his experience developing @RalstonCollege.⁣
⁣
Watch or listen via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/18/21.

node.title: University’s Forgotten Purpose to Illuminate Human Beings

node.text:
I hate conflict.⁣
⁣
But I'd rather have the small fight now, instead of letting it build-up - resulting in a worse fight in the future. Have the conflict now, and experience genuine peace later.⁣
⁣
Negotiation about who does what in a relationship can be tough, but it's worth it in the long run.⁣
⁣
Released 03/02/2021 - With @TimFerriss.

node.title: The Value of Fights in Relationships

@DrWarrenFarrell: "...Lois Lane had no interest in Clark Kent, but she fell in love with Superman. Once she fell in love with Superman, she wanted Superman to be able to cry and express emotions. But the man who did cry, express emotions and feelings and was sensitive, Clark Kent, she has zero interest in."⁣
⁣
To watch more of this conversation about men and boys issues, parenting, mental health and relationships, click the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.

⁣
This episode went live on Monday on my YouTube channel, Apple Podcasts and Spotify.⁣ Click my bio link to watch more:
⁣

What is it that you want from sex?⁣
⁣
Is it intimacy? Is it closeness? Do you want the person to pay attention to you?

Lust will get you somewhere but having somebody care about you is far more important.⁣
⁣
People are lonely - we need someone to communicate with, and we need someone to tie our lives together with when times are good to share triumphs and catastrophes when times are bad.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/02/2021 - with @OfficialBenShapiro.

I hate conflict.⁣
⁣
But I'd rather have the small fight now, instead of letting it build-up - resulting in a worse fight in the future. Have the conflict now, and experience genuine peace later.⁣
⁣
Negotiation about who does what in a relationship can be tough, but it's worth it in the long run.⁣
⁣
Released 03/02/2021 - With @TimFerriss.

⁣
To hear us talk more in-depth about these topics, head over to my YouTube channel and watch our conversation in full. Or, listen on Apple Podcasts or Spotify.⁣
⁣
